{{Chinese||s=薛平贵与王宝钏|t=薛平貴與王寶釧|p=Xuē Píngguì Yǔ Wāng Băochuān}}

'''''Love Amongst War''''' ({{zh|s=薛平贵与王宝钏}}) is a [[History of China|Chinese historical]] television series about the life of [[Xue Pinggui]], a legendary hero in [[Chinese folklore]], and based on the events in the Xiantong [[Chinese era name|era]] of [[Emperor Yizong of Tang|Emperor Yizong]] of the [[Tang dynasty]]. The series was written and produced by Jian Yuanxin, and directed by Lin Tianyi. The series stars [[Benny Chan (actor)|Benny Chan]], [[Jessica Hsuan]], and Angel Lou.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://video.xin.msn.com/watch/video/jessica-hsuan-dismisses-relationship-rumors-%E5%AE%A3%E8%90%B1-%E6%8A%A5%E7%BA%B8%E4%B8%8A%E4%BC%A0%E7%9A%84%E7%BB%AF%E9%97%BB%E7%94%B7%E5%8F%8B%E6%98%AF%E5%81%87%E7%9A%84/tn5xe23l |title=Jessica Hsuan dismisses relationship rumors! |accessdate= |publisher=MSN |work= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.popularasians.com/forum/t75035/ |title=Jessica Hsuan and Benny Chan Portray Lovers in "Love Amongst War"  |accessdate= |publisher= |work= }}</ref>

==Cast==
* [[Benny Chan (actor)|Benny Chan]] as [[Emperor Xuānzong of Tang]]/ [[Emperor Yizong of Tang|Xue Pinggui]].
* [[Jessica Hsuan]] as Wang Baochuan, the third daughter of Prime Minister, Xue Pinggui's wife, Empress of Tang Dynasty.
* Angel Lou as Dai Zhan, the Princess of Xiliang Kingdom, Xue Pinggui's concubine.

===Other===
* [[Yumiko Cheng]] as Xue Pinggui's mother, a concubine of [[Emperor Xuānzong of Tang]].
* Monica Mu as Concubine Yu, a concubine of Emperor Xuānzong of Tang.
* Hong Zhongyi as Wang Yun, Wang Baochuan's father, the Prime Minister of Tang Dynasty.
* Xue Shujie as Wang Baochuan's mother.
* Zhang Yongqi as Wang Jinchuan, the eldest daughter of Prime Minister Wang, Xue Baochuan's sister.
* Chen Yizhen as Wang Yinchuan, the second daughter of Prime Minister Wang, Xue Baochuan's sister.
* Johnny Zhang as Su Long, Wang Jinchuan's husband, the son-in-law of Prime Minister Wang.
* Lou Yajiang as Wei Hu, Wang Yinchuan's wife, the son-in-law of Prime Minister Wang.
* Candy Tu as Xue Qi, Xue Pinggui's sworn sister.
* Chen Weimin as Ge Da, Xue Pinggui's sworn brother.
* Zhang Liang as Wei Bao, Xue Qi's husband.
* Zhou Danli as Xiao Lian, Wang Baochuan's servant girl.
* Zhao Xi as the King of Xiliang Kingdom.
* Tai-Feng Hsia as the Empress of Xiliang Kingdom.
* Ye Zuxin as Ye Xing, the eunuch who saved Xue Pinggui.

==Release==
It was a hit TV drama in [[Mainland China]] and [[Taiwan]].

==Critical response==
The series received mixed reviews.

